The specificity of amplification was confirmed by gel electrophoresis of the P-sg-QPCR amplicons, followed by sequencing (data not shown). The P-sg-QPCR was able to detect all nine reference strains of FCoV as well as TGEV and CCoV. The melting point analysis revealed four different genetic variants in this very conserved region of the M gene with the following average temperature values: (1) 69.3 °C (UCD2, UCD3, UCD4, Black, 79-1146, DF-2); (2) 67.5 °C (UCD1); (3) 66.5 °C (NOR15, 79-1683, CCoV CB/05 and 144/01); (4) 63.6 (TGEV Purdue) (Table 3
; Fig. 2
).
